---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About LUTkyLab"
  description="LUTkyLab is a resource site for DJI creators — real-world reviews, color grading tutorials, buying guides, and free LUTs built from actual field experience."
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-[720px] px-4 sm:px-6 py-12">
    <div class="mb-10">
      <div class="w-20 h-20 rounded-lg bg-[#FF6B35] flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-3xl mb-6">LK</div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4">About LUTkyLab</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-[#9CA3AF]">Real-world resources for DJI creators.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose">
      <h2>What this site is</h2>
      <p>
        LUTkyLab is a resource site for people who shoot with DJI cameras — Pocket 3, Osmo, Action series, and drones. Everything here comes from real field use: actual footage tested, accessories purchased and tried, hours spent in DaVinci Resolve working out what D-Log M actually needs to look good.
      </p>

      <p>
        The goal is simple — write the guides and reviews that were missing when we were trying to figure this stuff out ourselves.
      </p>

      <h2>What you'll find here</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Reviews</strong> — Honest assessments of cameras and accessories, based on months of real use, not one-week embargo reviews.</li>
        <li><strong>Tutorials</strong> — Color grading workflows, camera settings, and export guides that actually apply to DJI footage.</li>
        <li><strong>Buying guides</strong> — Best-of lists for microSD cards, filters, mics, and accessories — tested before recommended.</li>
        <li><strong>Free LUTs</strong> — 40 LUTs built for DJI D-Log M footage. Works in DaVinci Resolve, Premiere Pro, and Final Cut Pro.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Why trust this?</h2>
      <p>
        Every accessory recommended on this site has been purchased and used. When something has a real weakness, we say so. Affiliate links are clearly disclosed. Sponsored content is labeled. The goal is a resource worth bookmarking — not a content farm.
      </p>

      <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      <p>
        Questions, corrections, or collaboration — use the <a href="/contact">contact page</a>. If you have a specific question about DJI footage or color grading, reach out. We genuinely like talking about this stuff.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
